entries.meaning: (military) Designed to attack a naval ship.
examples: A single EXOCET antiship missile can sink a destroyer. Try not to get hit.

entries.meaning: (fandom slang) Pertaining to the activities of antishippers

verbs.description: antiship (third-person singular simple present antiships, present participle antishipping, simple past and past participle antishipped)

entries.meaning: (fandom slang) To participate in the activities of anti-shippers
